textAfterTable: 18 Songs Biography Born: 03 April 1928 in Shelby, NC Genre: Country Years Active: '40s, '50s, '60s, '70s, '80s, '90s, '00s Singer/songwriter Don Gibson was one of the most popular and influential forces in '50s and '60s country, scoring numerous hit singles as a performer and a songwriter. Gibson's music touched on both traditional country and highly produced country-pop, which is part of the reason he had such a broad audience. For nearly a decade after his first hit single, "Sweet Dreams," in 1956, he was a reliable hitmaker, and many of his songs have become country classics —...
